Silver ions in AgNO3 are reduced to AgNps through the action of bioactive compounds present in teak leaf extract. By measuring the initial and final concentration of silver ions in synthesis mixture, the amount of Ag ions reduced to silver nanoparticles can be calculated [29, 30]. Hence, the yield of Ag nanoparticles can be determined. Residual silver ions present in the supernatant obtained after biosynthesis were determined using AAS (GBC-932 PLUS). The amount of residual silver ions was expressed as final concentration in mg/L and the percentage yield of AgNps based on initial Ag ions concentration in synthesis mixture was calculated using Eq. (1).1Percentageyield=ci-crci×100,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
