				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{Percentage}}\;{\text{yield}} = \left( {\frac{{c_{\text{i}} - c_{\text{r}} }}{{c_{\text{i}} }}} \right) \times 100,$$\end{document}where Ci is the initial concentration of Ag ions (mg/L) and Cr is the final residual concentration of Ag ions (mg/L).

X-ray diffractogram of biosynthesized AgNps is shown in Fig. 2. XRD analysis revealed the Face Centered Cubic structure of metallic crystalline AgNp; peaks belonging to (111), (200), (220), (311) and (211) planes of crystalline structure were observed in the diffractogram at 2θ values of 38.41, 44.75, 64.79, 77.31 and 81.85, respectively. The presence of these peaks agrees with the Braggs reflection of AgNps and indicates nanocrystalline structure of the silver particles biosynthesized by teak leaf extract. Broader peaks signify the formation of smaller nanoparticles. The size of the nanoparticles was calculated using Full width at half maximum data through Scherrer’s formula presented as Eq. (2):2D=Kλβ12cosθ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
