				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$D = \frac{K\lambda }{{\beta_{\frac{1}{2}} \cos \theta }}$$\end{document}Equation (2) uses the reference peak width at angle θ, where λ is the X-ray wavelength (1.5418 Å), β1/2 is the width of the XRD peak at half height and K is a shape factor (0.9). The average size of the AgNps was approximately calculated to be around 28.02 nm.Fig. 2
X- ray diffractogram of the biosynthesized silver nanoparticles by teak leaf extract

FTIR analysis was conducted on the biosynthesized AgNps and the IR spectra shown in Fig. 3 revealed a sharp peak at 2358 cm−1 which can be attributed to the N–H stretching vibrations, 1218.8 cm−1 to C–O stretching of polyols like hydroxyflavones, 1010 cm−1to C–N stretching vibrations of aliphatic amines or to alcohols and phenols indicating that phenols also play an important role in the reduction of the precursor salt. The peak at 1362.7 cm−1 indicates the presence of residual NO3-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
