				\begin{document}$${\text{NO}}_{3}^{ - }$$\end{document} along with the biosynthesized nanoparticles: 1580.4 cm−1 can be attributed to C–O stretching vibrations, while 2916.1 and 2848.5 cm−1 correspond to amide linkages. The fingerprint thus obtained suggests that bound and unbound amide linkages belonging to aromatic rings, ethers and polyphenols are the bioactive components that act as reducing and stabilizing agents towards the biosynthesized AgNps [43]. Researchers have attributed the bioactive components such as antioxidants, flavonoids, terpenes, acids, sugars and proteins to reduce the precursor salt as well as cap the biosynthesized AgNps [28].Fig. 3
